{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"symbolKind":"method","title":"initAsync(ioPriority:cancellable:callback:userData:)","externalID":"s:3GIO21AsyncInitableProtocolPAAE04initB010ioPriority11cancellable8callback8userDataySi_AA14CancellableRefVSgySpySo8_GObjectVGSg_SpySo13_GAsyncResultVGSgSvSgtXCSgATtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO14DBusConnectionC","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"initAsync"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"ioPriority","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"callback","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GAsyncReadyCallback","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"extendedModule":"GIO"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnection","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnection\/AsyncInitableProtocol-Implementations"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnection\/initasync(iopriority:cancellable:callback:userdata:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnection\/initAsync(ioPriority:cancellable:callback:userData:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Starts asynchronous initialization of the object implementing the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"interface. This must be done before any real use of the object after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"initial construction. If the object also implements "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" you can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"optionally call "},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"initAsync"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"ioPriority"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"callback"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback","text":"GAsyncReadyCallback","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userData"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method is intended for language bindings. If writing in C,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_async_initable_new_async()"},{"type":"text","text":" should typically be used instead."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When the initialization is finished, ","type":"text"},{"code":"callback","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be called. You can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then call ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_async_initable_init_finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to get the result of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initialization.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Implementations may also support cancellation. If ","type":"text"},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is not","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then initialization can be cancelled by triggering the cancellable","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"object from another thread. If the operation was cancelled, the error","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"text":" will be returned. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" is not ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the object doesn’t support cancellable initialization, the error"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"notSupported","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As with ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", if the object is not initialized, or initialization"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"returns with an error, then all operations on the object except","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref()"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" are considered to be invalid, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"have undefined behaviour. They will often fail with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_critical()"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_warning()"},{"type":"text","text":", but this must not be relied on."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Callers should not assume that a class which implements "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable"},{"text":" can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be initialized multiple times; for more information, see "},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If a class explicitly supports being initialized multiple times,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"implementation requires yielding all subsequent calls to ","type":"text"},{"code":"init_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results of the first call."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For classes that also support the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","type":"reference"},{"text":" interface, the default","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implementation of this method will run the ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in a thread, so if you want to support asynchronous initialization via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads, just implement the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" interface without overriding","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"any interface methods.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"sy